# Claude untracked privileged values
.claude/secret.md

# Local (this Mac) environment map — operator-local state, kept untracked on purpose.
.claude/ops/local/ENVIRONMENT_MAP.md

# Track the .claude experiments ops doc (override the broad `experiments/` ignore above)
!.claude/ops/experiments/
!.claude/ops/experiments/**

# agent_logs belong at the ABSOLUTE ~/Documents/agent_logs/, never in-repo.
# A relative agent_logs/ here is the recurring relative-path bug — ignore it so it can never be committed.
/agent_logs/

# Recurring transient cluster artifacts (Leonardo working-tree junk that keeps reappearing).
# A file literally named "&1" is a botched `2>&1` redirect that wrote to a file — never real output.
/&1
# Grid launch manifests under hpc/skyrl_yaml/leonardo/ are generated launch-logs (one line per
# submitted cell, from launch_*_grid.sh) — ephemeral run output, not curated inputs (those are the
# tracked *_grid_cells.txt). Regenerate by relaunching the grid.
hpc/skyrl_yaml/leonardo/*_manifest.txt

# Round 2 (2026-06-25): more recurring Leonardo working-tree junk.
# Editor/script backup copies (*.bak) — e.g. dataset_info.json.bak, sbatch_gsm8k_grid.sh.bak —
# are transient snapshots written by the launch drivers (launch_54.sh §9.4 cp-then-sed); the
# tracked file is the non-.bak original. No tracked .bak exists, so this is safe.
*.bak
# Per-sweep reeval campaign priority files (one model per file) are auto-generated each refill by
# the eval refill loop — ephemeral campaign scratch, regenerated, not curated. (The curated eval
# priority lists live under eval/lists/ and are tracked individually.)
reeval_priority_*.txt
# Wave-launch SLURM jobid dumps (one line per submitted cell, written by wave*_launch.sh) —
# per-run output, regenerated each launch. The reusable launchers themselves are tracked.
wave*_jobids.txt
# Repo-root gen_only_delphi.py is a leftover DUPLICATE of the canonical tracked
# scripts/gen_only_delphi.py (round-1 relocated it to scripts/). Anchored to root so it never
# re-enters git as a near-dup; the tracked scripts/ copy is unaffected.
/gen_only_delphi.py

# Round 3 (2026-06-26): the a1-* re-eval campaign auto-generates per-benchmark REFILL priority
# lists in eval/lists/ each refill cycle (one model name per file, e.g. refill_tb2_a1-bugswarm.txt,
# reeval_refill_java_swebench.txt). These are the eval/lists/ siblings of the already-ignored
# repo-root reeval_priority_*.txt — ephemeral campaign scratch, regenerated every refill by the
# active re-eval driver, NOT curated. The CURATED eval lists in eval/lists/ are tracked
# individually and do NOT match these prefixes, so this is surgical.
eval/lists/refill_tb2_a1-*.txt
eval/lists/reeval_refill_*.txt
# Also ignore the eval/lists/ copies of the reeval_priority_* campaign scratch (the existing
# unanchored reeval_priority_*.txt already covers these, but kept explicit for clarity).
eval/lists/reeval_priority_a1-*.txt
# Per-sweep reeval RELAUNCH priority lists (dated, e.g. eval/lists/reeval_relaunch_swe_20260627.txt) —
# the relaunch-path siblings of reeval_refill_*; regenerated each campaign relaunch, never tracked.
eval/lists/reeval_relaunch_*.txt
reeval_relaunch*.txt
# Repo-root per-sweep reeval REFILL scratch (dated, e.g. reeval_refill16_swe_20260626.txt /
# reeval_refill_swe2_20260626.txt) — regenerated every refill (the eval/lists/ copies are ignored above).
reeval_refill*.txt
# One-off dated wave-launch scaffolding (launch_wave1.sh / wave4_launch.sh / wave4_prep.sh) —
# transient per-wave campaign launchers; the durable launcher is eval/unified_eval_listener.py.
launch_wave*.sh
wave*_launch.sh
wave*_prep.sh

# Transient per-sweep generated eval priority-lists (regenerated each refill; not reusable artifacts)
eval/lists/a1_resume_*.txt
eval/lists/tacc_refill_*.txt
eval/lists/tacc_sanity_*.txt
eval/lists/reeval_priority_*.txt
